---
// Section 4 — See the linter at work.
// Visual callback to the hero: same green ✓ and red ✗ hex.
---

<section class="linter section" aria-labelledby="linter-title">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <h2 id="linter-title" class="linter__title">Run the linter.</h2>
    <p class="linter__intro">
      Run <code>specscore lint</code> against the spec you just saw.
      Here's what it tells you.
    </p>

    <div
      class="linter__terminal"
      role="img"
      aria-label="Terminal output of specscore lint: R1 and R2 pass with green checks, R3 fails with a red mark and a fixable error message."
    >
<pre class="terminal"><span class="prompt">$</span> specscore lint checkout/apply-discount.md

  checkout/apply-discount.md
    <span class="mark-pass">✓</span> R1  Single-code limit
    <span class="mark-pass">✓</span> R2  Code validity
    <span class="mark-fail">✗</span> R3  Discount application
         <span class="dim">AC-3:18</span>  ambiguous AC — "higher-of rule" doesn't specify the tiebreaker
                  <span class="dim">expected:</span> concrete tie-break behavior, or reference to a defined rule
                  <span class="dim">fix:</span>      specify "higher discount wins; if tied, site-wide promotion wins"

  <span class="dim">1 of 3 requirements failing</span>
  <span class="dim">exit 1</span></pre>
    </div>

    <p class="linter__caption">
      The green checks and the red ✗ in this output are the same marks
      you saw in the hero. The linter is what produces them.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .linter { background: var(--cream); }
  .linter__title {
    font-size: var(--fs-h2);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .linter__intro {
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
  .linter__intro code {
    background: var(--cream-2);
    padding: 0.05em 0.35em;
    border-radius: 2px;
    font-size: 0.92em;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .linter__terminal {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .linter__caption {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    max-width: 60ch;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
</style>
